<h2><a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/17/run-macos-vm-docker-on-windows-linux-docker-osx/" rel="bookmark" title="Run MacOS VM&#8217;s in Docker on Windows &#038; Linux with Docker-OSX">Run MacOS VM&#8217;s in Docker on Windows &#038; Linux with Docker-OSX</a></h2>
<div id="subhead_block">
<span class="subhead_lefty">Nov 17, 2023 - <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/17/run-macos-vm-docker-on-windows-linux-docker-osx/#respond">Leave a Comment</a></span>
<span class="subhead_righty"></span>
</div>

<div class="contenttext">

<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-610x305.jpg" alt="Docker-OSX Mac VM on Linux or Windows is possible" width="610" height="305" class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-large wp-image-127822" srcset="" data-srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-610x305.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-300x150.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-768x384.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-610x305.jpg" alt="Docker-OSX Mac VM on Linux or Windows is possible" width="610" height="305" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-127822" srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-610x305.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-300x150.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm-768x384.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/docker-osx-mac-vm.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></noscript></p>
<p>If you use Docker and virtual machines often, you may be happy to know that you can run MacOS VM&#8217;s in Docker, at near native performance atop Windows or Linux, thanks to an open source project called Docker-OSX. Yes, that means you can run MacOS on a PC, whether that PC is running Windows or Linux. Docker-OSX includes support for iMessage, and iPhone/iPad USB connections too, allowing for a robust MacOS experience, despite being on a PC.</p>
