<div class="contenttext">

<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-610x493.jpg" alt="FaceTime Reaction Effects and Gestures" width="610" height="493" class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-large wp-image-127780" srcset="" data-srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-610x493.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-300x243.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-768x621.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures.jpg 1123w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-610x493.jpg" alt="FaceTime Reaction Effects and Gestures" width="610" height="493" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-127780" srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-610x493.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-300x243.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures-768x621.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/facetime-reaction-effect-gestures.jpg 1123w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Apple has introduced all new reaction gestures for FaceTime on the iPhone, iPad, and Mac, meaning if you make certain hand gestures, symbols, or movements, you will trigger a digital effect reaction. For example, if you make a thumbs up gesture with your hand, a thumbs up emoji will appear on the screen, or if you make a peace sign, you&#8217;ll trigger balloons effects on the screen.</p>
<p>Many of these reaction gesture triggers and effects work in FaceTime video calls, but also Zoom video conferences, and some other video chat apps too.</p>
