<h2><a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/15/disable-click-wallpaper-show-desktop-macos/" rel="bookmark" title="How to Disable &#8220;Click Wallpaper to Show Desktop&#8221; in MacOS Sonoma">How to Disable &#8220;Click Wallpaper to Show Desktop&#8221; in MacOS Sonoma</a></h2>
<div id="subhead_block">
<span class="subhead_lefty">Nov 15, 2023 - <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/15/disable-click-wallpaper-show-desktop-macos/#respond">Leave a Comment</a></span>
<span class="subhead_righty"></span>
</div>

<div class="contenttext">

<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-610x395.jpg" alt="Click Wallpaper to Reveal Desktop on MacOS" width="610" height="395" class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-large wp-image-127774" srcset="" data-srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-610x395.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-300x194.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-768x497.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-1536x994.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-2048x1326.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-610x395.jpg" alt="Click Wallpaper to Reveal Desktop on MacOS" width="610" height="395" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-127774" srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-610x395.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-300x194.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-768x497.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-1536x994.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/click-to-reveal-desktop-macos-2048x1326.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></noscript></p>
<p>MacOS Sonoma introduced a feature on the Mac that activates Expose which hides all open windows and apps, whenever you click on the desktop. This feature happens seamlessly, and when you click on the desktop wallpaper, you&#8217;ll reveal the desktop by pushing aside all other open apps and their windows, thus revealing the desktop and its wallpaper. Some Mac users really like this new feature, and others are less impressed with it, and some may find the feature annoying.</p>
<p>If you do not want MacOS to show the desktop when you click on the wallpaper, you can turn off the click to reveal desktop feature in macOS Sonoma. </p>
<p> <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/15/disable-click-wallpaper-show-desktop-macos/" class="more-link">Read more &raquo;</a></p>



</div>



