<h2><a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/12/psa-content-blockers-may-break-captive-portal-wi-fi-login-pages/" rel="bookmark" title="PSA: Content Blockers May Break Captive Portal Wi-Fi Login Pages">PSA: Content Blockers May Break Captive Portal Wi-Fi Login Pages</a></h2>
<div id="subhead_block">
<span class="subhead_lefty">Nov 12, 2023 - <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/12/psa-content-blockers-may-break-captive-portal-wi-fi-login-pages/#respond">Leave a Comment</a></span>
<span class="subhead_righty"></span>
</div>

<div class="contenttext">

<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-610x416.jpg" alt="Content blockers may break captive portal wi-fi login pages" width="610" height="416" class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-large wp-image-127561" srcset="" data-srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-610x416.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-300x205.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-768x524.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-1536x1047.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login.jpg 2024w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-610x416.jpg" alt="Content blockers may break captive portal wi-fi login pages" width="610" height="416" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-127561" srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-610x416.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-300x205.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-768x524.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login-1536x1047.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/content-blocker-breaks-captive-portal-wifi-login.jpg 2024w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Here&#8217;s a helpful bit of knowledge that you may want to keep in mind when traveling or using public wi-fi spaces; if you use Content Blockers in Safari or your web browser, that content blocker may break a wi-fi&#8217;s captive portal login page, thereby preventing you from joining that particular wireless network. This applies to content blockers on any web browser and any Apple operating system, whether it&#8217;s a Mac, iPhone, iPad, or otherwise (and Windows too of course, but that&#8217;s not our focus here).</p>
<p> <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/12/psa-content-blockers-may-break-captive-portal-wi-fi-login-pages/" class="more-link">Read more &raquo;</a></p>



</div>



