</div>

<div class="contenttext">

<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-610x567.jpg" alt="Uber" width="610" height="567" class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-large wp-image-127720" srcset="" data-srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-610x567.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-300x279.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-768x714.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app.jpg 1028w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-610x567.jpg" alt="Uber" width="610" height="567" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-127720" srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-610x567.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-300x279.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app-768x714.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/uber-app.jpg 1028w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></noscript></p>
<p>Uber and Uber Eats are undeniably useful apps, allowing you to get a ride or have food delivered quickly and conveniently, right from your iPhone (or Android) either from the app or even <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2019/12/31/how-order-uber-iphone-siri/">from Siri</a>. But one thing that is very annoying and obnoxious about Uber and Uber Eats is that the apps default to sending you promo notifications and advertisement notifications, meaning you may get alerts on your phone from Uber and Uber Eats that are nothing but ads, promos, marketing material, or solicitations, and have nothing to do with a ride or delivery.</p>
<p>We&#8217;re going to show you how you can disable the annoying Uber promo notifications and ad alerts, while still keeping notifications for rides and other actually important stuff available on your device.</p>
<p> <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/11/how-to-turn-off-uber-promo-notifications-ads/" class="more-link">Read more &raquo;</a></p>



</div>



