<h2><a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/10/watchos-10-1-1-update-fixes-battery-drain-issue/" rel="bookmark" title="Apple Watch Battery Draining Rapidly? Don&#8217;t Miss the watchOS 10.1.1 Update">Apple Watch Battery Draining Rapidly? Don&#8217;t Miss the watchOS 10.1.1 Update</a></h2>
<div id="subhead_block">
<span class="subhead_lefty">Nov 10, 2023 - <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/10/watchos-10-1-1-update-fixes-battery-drain-issue/#respond">Leave a Comment</a></span>
<span class="subhead_righty"></span>
</div>

<div class="contenttext">

<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-610x463.jpg" alt="watchOS 10 on Apple Watch" width="610" height="463" class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-large wp-image-127154" srcset="" data-srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-610x463.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-300x228.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-768x583.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-1536x1166.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch.jpg 1596w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-610x463.jpg" alt="watchOS 10 on Apple Watch" width="610" height="463" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-127154" srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-610x463.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-300x228.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-768x583.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch-1536x1166.jpg 1536w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/watchos-10-apple-watch.jpg 1596w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></noscript></p>
<p>A fair number of Apple Watch users have been experiencing battery life issues lately, where the Apple Watch battery would drain much faster than expected or desired. In some instances, users would experience the Apple Watch battery draining from 100% to 50% or less in less than an hour, even with a perfectly <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2021/07/15/check-apple-watch-battery-health/">healthy battery</a>. </p>
<p>For the impacted Apple Watch owners, the devices poor battery performance began after updating to watchOS 10.1, and now Apple has released watchOS 10.1.1 update to fix that battery draining problem, which users should <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2015/06/26/update-apple-watch-os/">update to</a> right away when they get the chance.</p>
<p> <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/11/10/watchos-10-1-1-update-fixes-battery-drain-issue/" class="more-link">Read more &raquo;</a></p>



