<div class="contenttext">

<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/plugins/a3-lazy-load/assets/images/lazy_placeholder.gif" data-lazy-type="image" data-src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-610x471.jpg" alt="iPhone Standby Mode" width="610" height="471" class="lazy lazy-hidden aligncenter size-large wp-image-127689" srcset="" data-srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-610x471.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-300x232.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-768x593.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode.jpg 1122w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-610x471.jpg" alt="iPhone Standby Mode" width="610" height="471" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-127689" srcset="https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-610x471.jpg 610w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-300x232.jpg 300w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode-768x593.jpg 768w, https://cdn.osxdaily.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/iphone-standby-mode.jpg 1122w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" /></noscript></p>
<p>StandBy Mode is perhaps the most <a href="https://osxdaily.com/2023/10/05/best-new-tips-ios-17-features/">interesting feature</a> for iPhone users who update to iOS 17, transforming the iPhone into a customizable display clock whenever the iPhone is placed horizontally and is charging. </p>
<p>With StandBy Mode, your iPhone can become a table clock, a photo frame, an information display, amongst other possibilities, and since it&#8217;s easily customizable, how you use the feature is up to you.</p>
